<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c73">Consoles aren&#x27;t really a useful object. You can only play the heavily locked down titles the vendor approves for you, and nothing else. You have to pay a monthly subscription for the damn thing. And if you want to do anything at all than engage with the DRM lootbox subscription machine, no you don&#x27;t.<p>With this you can use the console to do anything that a PC can do. Which is literally everything.<p>You could, for instance, play all of your old legally-backed-up games without paying for them yet again. You could run productivity software, or play literally any game that isn&#x27;t blessed by Sony. It also doesn&#x27;t try to extract money from you at every opportunity.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=47955445&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D47952658%2347955445" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr class="athing comtr" id="47958097"><td><table border="0"><tr><td class="ind" indent="0"><img src="s.gif" height="1" width="0"></td><td valign="top" class="votelinks"><center><a id='up_47958097' href='vote?id=47958097&amp;how=up&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D47952658'><div class='votearrow' title='upvote'></div></a></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px;"><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=abrookewood" class="hnuser">abrookewood</a> <span class="age" title="2026-04-30T04:26:32 1777523192"><a href="item?id=47958097">10 hours ago</a></span> <span id="unv_47958097"></span><span class="navs"> | <a href="#47954025" class="clicky" aria-hidden="true">prev</a> | <a href="#47956510" class="clicky" aria-hidden="true">next</a> <a class="togg clicky" id="47958097" n="1" href="javascript:void(0)">[–]</a><span class="onstory"></span></span></span></div><br>
